narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I was able to vastly improve my ability to speak and read Indonesian as well as get a more robust introduction to Indonesian culture.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Bu is the courses biggest strength, she is an absolutely phenomenal professor, the course wouldn't be the same without her! I think the course material was interesting and challenging as well. I think better organization would help students better succeed on exams.
Instructor needs to be more organized

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Absolutely, if you are looking for a language to do at Yale and do not want to get crushed by the ridiculous workload of a class like French then Indonesian is the best!
